{
  "texts": [
    "Since these early days, machine learning models have grown substantially in complexity and opacity (Devlin et al., 2019; Krizhevsky et al., 2012; Dosovitskiy et al., 2021).",
    "Training datasets have also exploded in size (Black & Fredrikson, 2021).",
    "These factors combine to make training data influence analysis significantly more challenging where, for multilayer parametric models (e.g., neural networks), determining a single training instance's exact effect can be NP-complete in the worst case (Blum & Rivest, 1992).",
    "In practice, influence may not need to be measured exactly.",
    "Influence estimation methods provide an approximation of training instances' true influence."
  ]
}